content: The authors repeatedly caution that their results are specific to the dataset and experiment they ran. They call it a "purely empirical observation of applying a heuristic method to a specific dataset without any generalization guarantees to other market environments or trading datasets". Models using data from a noiseless quantum simulator performed slightly worse than models using the original classical data. This suggests that the quantum algorithm itself, in its ideal form, did not provide an advantage.
